node.text: A note on behalf of PIndigenous, the Indigenous community at Pinterest: We’re proud that Pinterest joins us in recognizing the United Nations International Day of World’s Indigenous Peoples. In honor of this day, we show our respect to our Indigenous relatives worldwide by acknowledging our people and traditions, showing our support as a company and as a community, and changing our logo to the color orange. We are proud to recognize Indigenous people, our history, our resiliency and in particular Indigenous children.  Head to the link in bio to discover more 🧡
